widgets_values: A masterpiece, ultra-detailed, photorealistic cinematic shot of a majestic, weathered 17th-century pirate galleon sailing on a calm open sea during a breathtaking golden hour sunset. The ship, with a hull of dark, salt-stained oak and intricate, ornate carvings on its stern, cuts cleanly through the deep blue water. Its massive, slightly tattered black sails are fully unfurled, catching the warm, golden light of the setting sun, which hangs low on the horizon. From the mainmast, a large, tattered black Jolly Roger flag, featuring a classic skull and crossbones, billows dramatically in the wind. The sunlight glistens on the wet deck and creates a brilliant, fiery reflection on the water's surface. Beneath the ship, the dark fins of several large sharks can be seen subtly cutting through the surface of the water, escorting the vessel. The shot is captured from a low angle at sea level, emphasizing the ship's immense scale and power against the vast, colorful sky. The mood is epic, adventurous, and stunningly beautiful., The whole photo is like early 2010s snapshot photo captured with a phone and uploaded to facebook, featuring dynamic natural lighting, and a neutral white color balance with washed out colors.

WELCOME TO THE V3 VERSION. SO DIFFERENT FROM V1 AND V2. REMOVING THE V1 BECAUSE IT LACKS VARIATION OF IMAGE MAKES IT USELESS.

WORKFLOW AIMS TO DEFEAT THE BACKGROUND BLUR COMPLETELY, MAKING VISUAL CONSISTENCY AND DETAIL, ALSO LESS TIME. MORE PROMPT FOLLOWER.I ADVICE YOU TO WAIT FOR THE END RESULT FOR YOUR SATISFACTION. THE FIRST AND UPSCALER OUTPUT IS SO DIFFERENT.

AND FIXED THE SEED PROBLEM. NOW MAKING SEED RANDOMIZE GIVES YOU VARIATION OF THE SAME PROMPT
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

Workflow is more magical than you think on quality.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Trying to make a video model to become perfect image generator was not a logical task. So the process was painful.

I tried many settings with high noise and low noise problem. It wasn't easy finding the right values and the "workflow" because it seperated in two with the lora, and two with the models which makes it nightmare.So know that this WF didn't come easily and had many tests. Although i have done these tests, it may not be the best value for your target image,just tried to find general value for everyone.Visual consistency is not 100% as a result. UPSCALER sampler is more prompt follower than first output sampler, it tries to fix what is wrong with the first image output

Do not forget to read all the notes on the workflow,for all the tips. If you liked the output my youtube link below for a sub :

nodes.title: Note ⚠️
widgets_values:
I do not recommend changing any settings Even the steps

BUT, you can change second sampler's eta from 0.75 to 0.50 do not go below 0.50, what is effect? 

For example if you make second sampler eta = 0.50,and trying to make many human at once, you can get problem with hands,faces and more.But you get more realistic image and more prompt following image as a result. So i suggest you to only change that depends on your image complexity, between 0.50 to 0.75.

Remember Second sampler's eta: 
0.50 more realistic,more mistakes,more prompt following

0.75 more ai like image,less realistic ,less prompt following, less mistakes.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
0.50 Usage example : portrait type,when there are not many components on the prompt."More simple prompt", when aiming realism,

0.75 Usage example : If the task to make more "ai" type of image. Less mistakes, less prompt following.

-------------------------------------------------------
If you get problem with the variation on different seed, maybe you can try lowering the highnoise lora strength to give more freedom to model. Because only variation factor is highnoise model.

nodes.title: PROMPT +
widgets_values: An ultra-detailed, photorealistic automotive photograph of a pearl white Nissan GT-R (R35), captured in a serene asphalt parking lot at the peak of golden hour. The car features custom black racing stripes on its side and an offset stripe on the trunk, a large gloss black rear wing spoiler, and gloss black multi-spoke aftermarket wheels. Shot from a low-angle, rear three-quarter view, its iconic quad circular taillights are illuminated and glowing a vibrant red, with its Ontario license plate reading "CXTC 719" clearly visible. The entire scene is bathed in the warm, magical light of the setting sun on the horizon, which creates a soft lens flare and casts gentle shadows across the asphalt and its painted white lines. The photographic style renders the car with extreme clarity and tack-sharp focus, drawing all attention to its details, while the background elements of light poles and a commercial building recede into a soft, atmospheric distance, creating a cinematic, masterpiece-quality image with a calm and beautiful atmosphere.The whole photo is like early 2010s snapshot photo captured with a phone and uploaded to facebook, featuring dynamic natural lighting, and a neutral white color balance with washed out colors.

So first of all,
The upscaler has no value that exists perfect for every image type. It is impossible and always will be that way.

Let me tell you the logic :

We upscale the latent and Resample it with Highnoise sampler at first phase with low denoise, it is because we do not want a new image, 0.62 is the value i am using so let's talk what will happen if you change that:

If you lower first sampler's denoise you'll get more noisy image. But more consistent image as for the first pass, the noise amount can broke your image or make more consistent depending on the target image.

If you make higher first sampler's denoise, you'll get less noisy image, less consistent image (But can do a complete new image, which is not desired.)

What will be the effect of this change to the second sampler? It is significant. The second sampler uses low noise model, but denoise is lower and it gets the latent from high noise pass, what is it mean? It means if the first sampler's noise amount is higher so the output will be more noisy.

--------------------------------------

Let's talk about second sampler's denoise level, it is even more important because it gets reference from noisy latent (first pass.),What about changing second sampler's denoise? so if you lower the denoise it get's more reference that means more noisy, (sometimes more detailed image) will be result. What if we make it higher? it is starting to get more freedom and tries to make new image completely, it has a breaker level that makes complete different image, assuming that level to be 0.65-0.70.

----------------------------------

So a portrait and landscape photo is complete different and its different best values exist for them, it is hard to get the best result with the same settings, sometimes you need to play with the values. If you get the logic, it is easy to play from that point.

-----------------------------------

However, we have now a new problem, it is contrast. Contrast of the image is higher than the input. It has no fix for now, i will put color match which can helps little to solve that problem. But still it exists.

------------------------------------------

You can try to make different version of this with Clownshark samplers, but you have to play with eta values, it can generate different results. May be more realistic, but problem becomes more challenging for the noise amount.
--------------------------------------
Great things take time.But do we have the opportunity to build them?
Changing the seed also give variation for the upscale phase, note it.

So a 0.55 and 0.55 for both samplers can be better for portrait, but it is not a great value for image with too much components.

0.62 - 0.55 is great for many image types.

Look note upside for more information.
